-- Commerzbank nears sale of Spanish property loans -sources
-- 
-- Tue May 20, 2014 03:22AM EDT
-- None



FRANKFURT, May 20 (Reuters) - Germany's Commerzbank <CBKG.DE> is close to selling a package of about 4.2 billion euros ($5.8 billion) in Spanish property loans at a discount to JP Morgan <JPM.N> and Lone Star, financial sources said.

The sale price is between 3.7 billion euros and 3.9 billion euros, the sources said.  Spanish newspaper Expansion earlier on Tuesday reported that a sale agreement was in the offing, citing a sale price of 3.5 billion euros. Commerzbank and Lone Star declined comment. JP Morgan was not immediately available for comment.